{"questionId":"26730","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An electric circuit has two power sources. The voltage, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, provided by the first power source, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>, is modelled by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mtext>Re</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>t</mi><mtext>i</mtext></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>The voltage, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>, provided by the second power source is modelled by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mtext>Re</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo><mtext>i</mtext></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>The total voltage in the circuit, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>T</mi></msub></math>, is given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence write down the maximum voltage in the circuit.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>maximum voltage is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99088</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(units)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26730","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ2.13b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence write down the maximum voltage in the circuit.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers introduction","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}